.TH XTGEOIP 1 "" "xtgeoip 3.1" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
xtgeoip \- Build and manage xt_geoip data from MaxMind GeoLite2 CSVs.
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B xtgeoip
[\fB\-b\fR] [\fB\-c\fR] [\fB\-p\fR] [\fB\-f\fR]
.br
.B xtgeoip
\fIcommand\fR [\fIoptions\fR]
.SH DESCRIPTION
\fBxtgeoip\fR downloads MaxMind GeoLite2 CSV databases and converts them into binary IP range files for the Linux xt_geoip kernel module.
.SH COMMANDS
.TP
.BI "build " "[\fB\-b\fR] [\fB\-c\fR] [\fB\-p\fR] [\fB\-f\fR] [\fB\-l\fR]"
Build xt_geoip database
.TP
.BI "conf" " \fB\-d\fR|\fB\-e\fR|\fB\-s\fR"
Manage configuration
.RS
.TP
.B \-d
Delete configuration
.TP
.B \-e
Edit configuration
.TP
.B \-s
Show configuration
.RE
.TP
.BI "fetch " "[\fB\-p\fR]"
Fetch GeoLite2 data files
.TP
.BI "run " "[\fB\-b\fR] [\fB\-c\fR] [\fB\-p\fR] [\fB\-f\fR] [\fB\-l\fR]"
Run full pipeline
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-b ", " \-\-backup
Back up current database before replacing it.
.TP
.BR \-c ", " \-\-clean
Clean working files before continuing.
.TP
.BR \-f ", " \-\-force
Force the relevant operation when supported.
.TP
.BR \-l ", " \-\-legacy
Enable legacy mode.
.TP
.BR \-p ", " \-\-prune
Prune retained artifacts for the current operation.
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
.B xtgeoip -h
display usage
.TP
.B xtgeoip -b
backup database
.TP
.B xtgeoip -c
clean database
.TP
.B xtgeoip -b -c
backup then clean
.TP
.B xtgeoip -b -p
backup then prune
.TP
.B xtgeoip build
build database
.TP
.B xtgeoip build -l
build (legacy mode)
.TP
.B xtgeoip build -b -p
backup then prune then build
.TP
.B xtgeoip build -c -f
clean then build
.TP
.B xtgeoip build -b -c -p
backup, prune, clean, build
.TP
.B xtgeoip conf -s
show configuration
.TP
.B xtgeoip conf -d
show default configuration
.TP
.B xtgeoip conf -e
edit configuration
.TP
.B xtgeoip fetch
fetch CSVs
.TP
.B xtgeoip fetch -p
fetch then prune archives
.TP
.B xtgeoip run
fetch then build
.TP
.B xtgeoip run -l
fetch then build (legacy)
.TP
.B xtgeoip run -p
fetch then prune then build
.TP
.B xtgeoip run -c -p
clean then fetch then prune then build
.TP
.B xtgeoip run -c -f
force clean then fetch then build
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR xt_geoip (8),
.BR iptables (8)
